{"ts": "2026-04-22T22:04:34Z", "event": "clarify_critic", "feature": "codify-citation-norm-and-premise-as-verification-in-discovery-research-phase", "findings": ["Intent clarity HIGH claim rests on 'gaps named' and 'observable outcomes stated', but the ticket cites three different line ranges (research.md:35-42, 67-73, 104-107) as sites of weakness without saying which of them must change, leaving the mechanism (new subsection vs. rewrite of \u00a75 vs. template change) unspecified \u2014 multiple incompatible rule designs could satisfy the stated outcomes.", "The ticket introduces a new artifact token `premise-unverified` in its success criteria without defining its syntactic shape, location, or producer; since #139 is described as reading this signal, the shape is a contract that the HIGH rating treats as settled when it is implicit.", "Scope boundedness HIGH takes the ticket's 'standalone rule edit in a single file' claim at face value, but the rule 'empty-corpus searches reported as a distinct outcome' logically requires knowing whether a codebase-agent search returned empty vs. skipped \u2014 a signal that may require contract changes at skills/research/ or the codebase-agent prompt.", "Scope boundedness treats #139 as 'downstream gating, not a bundle requirement' by repeating the ticket's phrase, but #139 is described as reading `premise-unverified` \u2014 a producer/consumer API coupling, not a soft blocker.", "Requirements alignment HIGH \u2014 ALIGNED is supported only by one tangentially-relevant sentence in project.md; no requirements doc governs /discovery authoring rules specifically, so 'no conflicts across four docs' is being collapsed with 'positive alignment with a governing requirement'.", "Complexity 'simple \u2014 no behavioral coupling with callers' contradicts the Dependencies section stating #139 reads the `premise-unverified` signal this ticket introduces \u2014 textbook behavioral coupling; the 'single-file edit' reasoning describes the diff surface, not the design surface.", "Criticality 'high' reasoning ('shared skill infrastructure read by #139') contradicts the complexity rating's 'no behavioral coupling' \u2014 same coupling surface, two inconsistent readings.", "The assessment accepts the ticket's self-declared enforcement-at-synthesis boundary uncritically; the synthesis author is the same agent that produced the failing 83% artifact, and a post-hoc checklist might catch empty-corpus reporting more reliably than a synthesis-time rule."], "dispositions": {"apply": 2, "dismiss": 6, "ask": 0}, "applied_fixes": ["Revised complexity from simple to complex (F6): feature introduces a new contract token read by downstream #139, modifies shared /discovery skill infrastructure governing all future research artifacts, requires design judgment on Prerequisites-column retargeting, and introduces a new marker pattern \u2014 meets the complex criteria for shared infrastructure, cross-cutting effects, design trade-offs, and new-pattern introduction.", "Refined requirements alignment note (F5): from 'HIGH \u2014 ALIGNED, no conflicts' to 'HIGH \u2014 aligned with project.md principle (Research before asking, don't fill unknowns with assumptions); no /discovery-specific governing requirement exists, so alignment is principle-level rather than constraint-level'. HIGH rating retained because 'aligns with requirements/ context; no conflicts detected' is still met."], "dismissals": [{"finding_index": 0, "rationale": "Intent clarity measures goal unambiguity, not mechanism pre-specification. The three success criteria define observable outcomes a completed research.md must satisfy. Mechanism-level design choices (subsection placement, \u00a75 rewrite vs. template change) are spec-phase concerns."}, {"finding_index": 1, "rationale": "Token-shape specification is spec-phase contract design, not clarify-phase ambiguity. The goal (establish a premise-unverified signal) is clear; the shape will be pinned in spec and consumed by #139 per normal producer/consumer ordering."}, {"finding_index": 2, "rationale": "Self-resolved from Ask: the source material explicitly scopes work to 'standalone rule edit in a single file' (`skills/discovery/references/research.md`), and the feasibility table's Approach A confirms 'Pure edit to research.md. Prerequisites: None'. Empty-corpus reporting is enforceable synthesis-side (the author knows what searches were dispatched; claims must cite results or mark premise-unverified); no codebase-agent contract change required."}, {"finding_index": 3, "rationale": "The #138 \u2192 #139 relationship is normal topological ordering: #138 ships the producer signal first, #139 consumes whatever shape #138's spec pins. This is correct lifecycle flow, not a scope-bundling hazard."}, {"finding_index": 6, "rationale": "Resolved by F6's apply: revising complexity to complex eliminates the cross-rating inconsistency. Criticality stays high, now coherent with complexity=complex."}, {"finding_index": 7, "rationale": "The enforcement-at-synthesis vs. post-hoc-checklist decision is a load-bearing epic-level choice in DR-1 and DR-2 of research/audit-and-improve-discovery-skill-rigor/research.md: Approach B (post-hoc checklist) was explicitly rejected on empirical grounds (events.log showed post-hoc human checks did not catch #092), and Approach F (mechanical grounding) was deferred. Re-litigating at the #138 clarify level is out of scope."}], "status": "ok"}
